I've seen it said that the only reason this wasn't another AstroWorld was because #ARMY is historically nice and supportive. Won't argue with the reputation, but I also argue that a seated event like this was the bigger factor. Everyone knew their finish line.

Mileage may vary on your security line obviously, but I do not blame the staff or hold this against them. Just like with AstroWorld they didn't have the manpower or the training to handle the surge. This required immediate decisions they just couldn't make or act on unfortunately

But the lesson here, when coupled with AstroWorld, is not one of training (although that would help), but hiring. I know that's easy to say because if people don't apply there isn't anything you can do, but as live entertainment reopens, we need to understand the power of numbers
